Last week, I lost one of my biggest role models. My grandma Stoney was kind, quick, elegant, and wise. It’s a very weird feeling when we lose someone who is a pillar in your life because I’ve only ever known a world with her in it.

I was fortunate enough to spend about a week with her last month and during that time I spent a lot of time looking up at the stars. It’s something I did a lot as a child and I realized I really hadn’t been able to enjoy them in New Orleans. I chalked it up to the trading ports operating at all hours and the lights coming from them. I remember thinking “wow, I wish I could see stars like this back in New Orleans”.

Last weekend, I was grabbing something outside and for some reason, I felt the urge to look up. I was able to see the same constellations that I saw in Grandma Stoney’s yard. Whether she sent them to me or I felt the urge to take that second and look up, I realized that the people you love and the things that remind you of them are all around - you just have to pay attention. 

For my dad, I find he sends me songs on the radio that we’re his favorite to tell me I’m following the right path. For Stoney, and no surprise here, it’s millions of bright stars in the sky.

Take some time this weekend, slow down, look up, and feel the presence of those you’ve lost around you because it’s a powerful thing.

.
.
I got her out of that summer drought and into the fall season looking hot !! 
.
We ended up chopping a lot of the dead ends and then some. I started off with like two inches off the bottom and recreating that bob-ish looking shape. 
.
The back I took a little extra length from and added a nice streamline straight to the front. The reason it’s not a bob persaaaay is because I took that lil angle out of the front and made it straight on both sides. 
.
.
Also this girly has got some hair !! 
.
So with that said, I texturized the inner areas of her hair where I felt the most bulk. That allows our shape to be more modern and less bubbly. Then on the top area I lightened up the bulk with layers AND THEN texturized into that as well. 
.
It came out soooo good and of course we have to hydrate after!
.
This is where the gloss comes into action. I decided on a clear gloss to help deeply hydrate the hair and add tonssss of shine. This can be done even if you don’t have any color in your hair 😉
.
.

It’s been 4 years without my dad today. ❤️‍🩹

I always say that Grief is a weird thing because sometimes it feels like it happened 20 years ago and sometimes it feels like it happened yesterday and sometimes it feels like it hasn’t happened at all. And at any moment my dad will just call me up randomly to tell me one thing and hang up in his typical Sam way. ❤️‍🩹

The first photo is a new to me photo. It’s from my first birthday. And my grandma who I lost earlier this year found it for me and gave it to me when I was visiting her during her final days. And it’s so hard not to have tears streaming down my face as I write that because we always feel like we’re going to have forever with the people that we love and I’m sorry to say that, that is not the case. ❤️‍🩹

So please hug the people you love a little tighter today. Please tell people how you feel about them even if it seems silly to. Please don’t let grudges keep you from spending time with them. Because time is fleeting. 🫶🏼

I miss you dad. ❤️‍🩹
